			<ns0:name>bradnelson@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/bradnelson@google.com/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Currently the more correct we make untrusted.gypi in terms of pulling in host includes and defines, the more the host environment can influence how untrusted modules get built.
We have worked around most relevant cases, but this is less than ideal.
We should try to mitigate this more, perhaps by redefining OS at some high level, or moving to use of a TARGET_OS variable everywhere (or keeping OS as target and changing what gyp injects).
